  "text": "where · is the vector norm. It has been known in the screw theory of robotics [CITATION_1] that every rigid motion is a screw motion that can be realized as the exponential of a twist (i.e. a infinitesimal generator)ξ, with its components ω and ν corresponding to the angular velocity and translation velocity of the segment (i.e. bone) around its joint, respectively.",
